# Hermetic env overrides for `bun test`.
#
# Bun auto-loads `.env` for every process it starts, including `bun test`
# (which forces NODE_ENV=test regardless of what NODE_ENV a local `.env`
# sets). That means a contributor's personal `.env` — e.g. the documented
# SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE=false escape hatch used to run `bun dev` over plain
# http://localhost — silently leaks into the test process and corrupts tests
# that assert the secure-by-default config values (config.ts:
# `sessionCookieSecure: process.env.SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE !== "false"`).
#
# Bun applies `.env.test` on top of `.env` when NODE_ENV=test, so pinning the
# security-sensitive defaults here makes `bun test` deterministic no matter
# what a contributor has locally in their (gitignored) `.env`. This file IS
# committed (see the `!.env.test` exception in .gitignore) — unlike `.env`,
# it must contain no secrets, only safe/default test overrides.
SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE=true
